cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper focuses on Internet-based simulation of mobile ad hoc networks, which involves distributed simulation and communication among execution units. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses load balancing strategies and adaptive partitioning of the simulated model, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed). The evaluation of the scalability of the simulator involves system-level analysis and optimization, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the viability of the approach to build Internet-based simulations, which could be related to performance analysis and optimization (cs.PF).
